&gt; even before Pearl Harbour, which brought it into conflict with the
&gt; Germans.
&gt; What was the first time that the two navies directly engaged each other?
">

Generally reckoned to be September 4, 1941 when USS Greer and U-652
engaged each other with depth charges and torpedoes respectively.

Ultimately without effect to either.

Looser definitions of "navies directly engaged" might yield earlier
dates - for instance, the British PBY which relocated the Bismarck in
May, 1941, was piloted by an American naval officer.

Cheers,
