Not quite. Hitler engaged in an air supremacy war with the UK in 1940 and
lost. German surface ships were largely useless as they would be hunted down
and sunk in open sea by the Royal Navy. The Royal Navy had in place an
effective sea blockade on Germany. British bombers were bombing Germany.
Just before Pearl Harbour the Germans were defeated at Moscow with the USSR
taking 30,000 prisoners.

The Germans were going nowhere on both fronts and nowhere positive in the
desert too. Declaring war with the USA, for Germany meant they could openly
now attack US ships and convoys.  Their only real successes were in U-Boat
warfare at the time. Germany though it could make the merchant fleets of the
UK and USA ineffective. Doing that would starve the UK of raw materials and
US made equipment, reducing any threat in the west and in the desert,
